article.headline: Drake 67, Missouri St. 49
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Senior forward Jonathan Cox scored 23 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead Drake past Missouri State 67-49 on Wednesday. Guard Josh Young added 16 points for the Bulldogs (10-4, 1-1 Missouri Valley). Bouncing back from a 76-65 loss to Evansville on Sunday, the Bulldogs closed the first half on a 25-10 run and cruised to their first Valley win. Drake held the Bears (7-6, 0-2) to just 38.3 percent shooting from the floor and a season low for points. It also marked the fewest points Drake had allowed in a Valley regular-season game since a 45-41 home win against Illinois State in 2006. Freshman Kyle Weems led Missouri State with 13 points and nine rebounds. Senior forward Wade Knapp added 11 points and seven rebounds.
